    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Protocol Configuration Options handling in ESM bearer context accept messages\n\n### Summary\nWhen sending Activate Dedicated EPS Bearer Context Accept messages, the esm_send_activate_dedicated_eps_bearer_context_accept() function was clearing the presencemask field, which removed any Protocol Configuration Options that had been set by the calling code. This caused the UE to not echo back PCO from network requests, violating 3GPP TS 24.301 requirements.\n\nSimilar issue existed in the default bearer context accept function.\n\nThis fix preserves any existing PCO configuration by not resetting the presencemask field.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/ESM/SAP/esm_send.c`: Removed msg->presencemask = 0 initialization from both esm_send_activate_dedicated_eps_bearer_context_accept() and esm_send_activate_default_eps_bearer_context_accept() functions\n- Added comments explaining that presencemask is preserved to allow PCO to be passed through\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Call esm_send_activate_dedicated_eps_bearer_context_accept() with a message structure that has Protocol Configuration Options set\n2. Observe that after the function returns, the presencemask field is cleared to 0\n3. The PCO that was configured before the call is lost\n\nExpected behavior: PCO configuration should be preserved when set by calling code, as the network expects these options to be echoed back in accept messages.\n\n"
}